{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017segCS6VPpChtnyXGLKGVb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All requirements are met. Here's a summary of what was done and why:\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. **Fixed `app-user` configure permission on `/app`** — the configure field was empty (`\"\"`), blocking queue declare/bind operations. Set to `.*`.\n\n2. **Removed `ops-user` from `/app`** — ops-user had full permissions on `/app` (cross-vhost leak). Cleared with `clear_permissions`.\n\n3. **Granted `ops-user` full permissions on `/ops`** — ops-user had zero permissions on its own vhost, causing `ops-client` to crash. Set configure/write/read to `.*`.\n\n4. **Deleted the mis-declared `app-queue`** — a setup job had pre-created `app-queue` with `x-queue-mode: lazy`, but `app-client` tries to declare it without that arg. RabbitMQ rejects re-declaration with inequivalent args, so the queue was deleted via the management API, allowing the client to re-create it correctly on the next restart.\n\n**Final state:**\n- `/app`: only `app-user` has `.*`/`.*`/`.*`; `ops-user` has no access\n- `/ops`: only `ops-user` has `.*`/`.*`/`.*`; `app-user` has no access\n- `app-client` and `ops-client`: both `1/1 Running`\n- 3-node RabbitMQ cluster: all nodes healthy"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":763,"cache_read_input_tokens":38499,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":763},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b28aea30-bece-4098-8beb-1e3248b2ccef","uuid":"16a748b0-927b-4512-9c3a-581eb7a9b55c","request_id":"req_011CcdFk95bXq4UbyNmkSaie"}
